nasa-rm-standard pack — content licence
========================================

This pack is derived from:
    NASA Reliability and Maintainability (R&M) Standard for Spaceflight and
    Support Systems
    NASA (National Aeronautics and Space Administration)
    NASA-STD-8729.1A, Revision A — Approved 2017-06-13
    (superseding NASA-STD-8729.1)

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work, 17 U.S.C. 105).
(tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This source is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the National
Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA), and is therefore NOT subject to
copyright protection in the United States (17 U.S.C. 105). It is in the public
domain: anyone may reproduce, transform, and redistribute it for any purpose,
including commercially, without permission and without a share-alike obligation.

Attribution to NASA is provided as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE), not a
legal obligation. NASA does not endorse this pack or its authors, and the NASA
name and insignia are not used to imply endorsement.

Caveat carried forward: NASA-STD-8729.1A specifies R&M *objectives and strategies*,
not prescribed processes; detailed analysis procedures live in the referenced NASA
Preferred Reliability Practices (outside this source), and facility R&M is excluded.

